---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import OnboardingWizard from '../components/OnboardingWizard';
---

<Base
  title="Career Review · 5 Whys Career Studio"
  description="Take a quick career review to choose the right 5 Whys tool for your current goal, from reflection to resume polish, networking practice, or interview prep."
  theme="night"
  noindex={true}
>
  <div class="relative mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-4 py-8 sm:py-12 reveal">
    <h1 class="sr-only">Career Review Starting Point</h1>
    <p class="sr-only">
      The 5 Whys Career Studio start page helps visitors choose a focused career reflection path
      before using the resume bullet game, networking practice studio, interview preparation
      workspace, career dashboard, and guided five whys reflection tool. It is a private
      browser-based starting point for sorting goals, selecting the right exercise, and moving into
      a practical career workflow without an account. The page keeps onboarding narrow, fast, and
      local so each visitor can decide whether they need resume polish, interview practice,
      networking rehearsal, or deeper career direction. It explains the relationship between the
      studio tools, preserves a clear path back to the dashboard, and gives search crawlers a static
      description of the client-rendered onboarding experience. The workflow is intended for
      students, early career candidates, technical job seekers, and people trying to turn scattered
      career notes into a specific next action. It describes how a short career review can turn
      uncertainty into a recommended route, whether the visitor wants to refine a resume bullet,
      prepare interview stories, practice professional conversation, revisit long-term motivation,
      or open the progress dashboard. The hidden summary keeps the server-rendered page meaningful
      before the interactive wizard loads, while preserving the same visible interface, controls,
      and page design for people using the app.
    </p>
    <p class="sr-only">
      The career review route also gives static context for navigation, privacy, accessibility, and
      crawl analysis. It links the studio's visible product surface to its purpose: helping a
      visitor choose the right career exercise, save time before an application or conversation, and
      continue into a focused tool instead of guessing where to begin. The interactive wizard may
      change based on answers, but the underlying page remains a stable entry point for career
      planning, resume review, networking preparation, interview readiness, and personal reflection.
    </p>
    <p class="sr-only">
      It also supports technical SEO checks by providing durable server-rendered context for the
      page title, description, heading, privacy model, tool relationships, and navigation purpose
      before the React onboarding component becomes interactive.
    </p>
    <OnboardingWizard client:only="react" />
  </div>
</Base>
